Send a, you know, what's the...

20:42.658 --> 20:44.493
- A telegram?
- A telegram.

20:46.245 --> 20:47.579
Is there anything you can't do?

20:49.164 --> 20:50.832
It's gonna be one hell of a wedding.

20:50.916 --> 20:52.960
Garth, you have a phone call
in the infirmary.

20:53.043 --> 20:54.503
- For me?
- Yeah.

20:54.586 --> 20:57.506
Here in the States, "You have a call"
means the call is for you.

20:57.589 --> 21:00.592
- Yeah.
- Oh, stay here, darling. All right?

21:00.676 --> 21:02.678
Don't move... Literally.

21:03.595 --> 21:05.315
- I don't want you to move a muscle.
- Okay.

21:05.347 --> 21:07.474
- Very still. Motionless.
- All right.

21:07.557 --> 21:09.142
Be right back.

21:12.729 --> 21:14.731
- Claire, I really need to talk to you.
- What?

21:14.815 --> 21:17.651
You were right about everything.
Renata's a total psycho.

21:17.734 --> 21:19.987
- I never said that.
- Claire, look at me!

21:20.070 --> 21:23.031
It's just like you warned.
She bought a knife. She's dangerous.

21:23.115 --> 21:25.355
- We have to figure out what she's up to.
- Are you sure?

21:25.409 --> 21:28.453
I'm 100% sure.
I've never been more sure of anything.

21:28.537 --> 21:30.622
I need your help.
We're in this together now.

21:30.706 --> 21:33.208
We are? What do you mean? In what?

21:33.292 --> 21:37.004
No matter how weird or awful things get,
it's you and me, fifty-fifty.

21:37.087 --> 21:38.588
Oh, I don't agree to that.

21:38.672 --> 21:39.715
- Fifty-fifty.
- No.

21:39.798 --> 21:41.842
- Claire, fifty-fifty.
- Absolutely not.

21:41.925 --> 21:43.302
- Fifty-fifty!
- Stop saying it.

21:43.385 --> 21:44.886
- Claire.
- I will not agree.

21:44.970 --> 21:46.096
